@node Main "Ocqua - Documentation"

                               'Ocqua' 1.1

                           by Charles-N. Jacob

  'Ocqua', a @{" Workbench game " link play}, is played on a 10 by 10 tiles board.
The idea is to line 5 tiles or more with the same pattern, either
horizontally, vertically or diagonally. The more tiles you line up,
the more points you get. When a series of 5 or more tiles is made up,
the entire lineup is removed.

  Each time you move a tile and it doesn't make a series of at
least 5 similar tiles, 3 more tiles are randomly placed on the
board. Be careful not to let the board fill up completely because
when that happens, the game is over.

  Have fun!

