@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Ocqua" where you want on
your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or Libraries
are needed. The only requirement is that your Workbench must have at
least 8 colours.

                             How to play?

  To play, click on a tile containing the shape you want to move and
while holding the mousebutton, move the mousepointer until it gets to
an empty tile where you want to place the shape, then, release the
mousebutton (in a drag and drop manner).

  When you align 5 or more tiles with the same shapes, all these shapes
disappear and you get points according to the number of shapes that were
lined up, as is shown below:

       5 shapes   =   50 points
       6 shapes   =  120 points
       7 shapes   =  280 points
       8 shapes   =  640 points
       9 shapes   = 1440 points

  Each time  you move a tile and it doesn't make a series of at least 5
similar tiles, 3 more tiles are randomly placed on the board. If one of
these tiles creates a series of 5 or more similar tiles, that series will
be removed from the board, but you will get no points.

  If you place a tile in the center of two or three lineups (all with the
same shapes, of course), the points for each lineup will be added
successively, for example:

                   x             x
                   x             x
               x x . x x  -> x x @{b}x@{ub} x x     x = tile with a shape
                   x             x          . = empty tile
                   x             x

  The score will be 100 points (2 times 50 points).

  If you successfully clear the board of all the tiles, you get a
double-score bonus and the game ends.

  Have fun!

